    <div class="card" style="padding: 10%">
        <div class="card-header"><h2>How to Play</h2></div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p class="card-text">
                <ul>
                    <li>Each week, teams will gain or lose points according to their selected starting lineup.</li>
                    <li>Only the three players within a starting lineup qualify for points, so choose your players for that week wisely.</li>
                    <li>At the end of each week, each team will total up their points to be posted on the "Rankings" page by the commissioner.</li>
                    <li>The "Rankings" page is the home to all of the player and team stats.</li>
                    <li>Users are allowed to make trades amongst the other teams throughout the season.</li>
                    <li>If someone's team has no players left in the show, they are eliminated from the competition.</li>
                    <li>The team with the most points by the end of the season wins Fantasy Bachelor.</li>
                    <li>For the most optimal playing experience, limit your league to four teams or less.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <h4 class="card-title">First Episode</h4>
            <p class="card-text">
            <ul>
                <li>Drafting will take place after watching the premier of "The Bachelor".</li>
                <li>The elected commissioner will be in charge of organizing the draft.</li>
                <li>Every user in a league will take turns choosing a girl/boy from the cast until there is none remaining.</li>
                <li>Each user will upload their drafted contestants to the "My Team" page.</li>
            </ul>   
            </p>
            <h4 class="card-title">Each Episode</h4>
            <p class="card-text">
            <ul>
                <li>Each user will pick three "players" from their team as that week's starting lineup</li>
                <li>The starting lineup must be selected prior to watching the upcoming episode.</li>
                <li>The commissioner will be in charge of documenting points per players for verification purposes.</li>
                <li>Each user is responsible for uploading the points gained for their team.</li>
                <li>The commissioner is responsible for updating the "Rankings" page to correctly reflect each team's stats.</li>
            </ul>   
            </p>
        </div>
